M|mia|```bash
M|mia|npx tsc --noEmit
M|mia|npm run lint
M|mia|```
M|mia|> Note: Use `npx tsc --noEmit` in the Linux VM. `npm run build` is Windows-only (SWC binary).
M|mia|- Mia runs `npx tsc --noEmit` after every component she builds
M|mia|- If TypeScript check fails on her component: read the error, fix the type, run again
M|mia|- `npm run lint` must pass — watch for: missing `key` props in lists, unused imports, `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`
M|mia|| Error | Cause | Fix |
M|mia||-------|-------|-----|
M|mia|| `'use client'` error | Using hooks in a Server Component | Add `'use client'` at the top of the file |
M|mia|| Missing `key` in list | Mapping without key prop | Add `key={item.id}` to the mapped element |
M|mia|| Type mismatch on API rsp | rsp shape doesn't match contract | Check API contracts in Dev's mem.md, update component's expected type |
M|mia|| Tailwind class not applying | Using a dynamic class string | Use full class names — Tailwind purges dynamic strings |
M|mia|Before committing any component, Mia asks herself:
M|mia|1. Does this use `var(--color-*)` tokens? No hardcoded hex values?
M|mia|2. Is this responsive (mobile-first)?
M|mia|3. Are interactive elements keyboard-accessible?
M|mia|4. Does this match the dark cyberpunk style of the rest of the dashboard?
M|mia|```bash
M|mia|git push        # Requires Dev's sign-off
M|mia|npm run dev     # Mia may use this locally for visual verification only
M|mia|```
M|mia|When Mia's frontend tasks are complete and `npx tsc --noEmit` + `npm run lint` both pass, Mia logs the task in her mem.md and notifies Quinn to begin her QA rv.
M|mia|> Updated by SIP after task completion. Proven commands stay. Failed or deprecated commands are removed.
M|mia|> Rule: do not add new commands without removing or condensing an equivalent amount of cnt.
